Html:
I've been making any additions I need to make to the ModernWindow in FirstFloor.ModernUI/Themes/ModernWindow.xaml. For example, I modified the re-size grip at the bottom of the page to be a colored status bar more like what Visual Studio 2012 has:<br />
<pre><code>&lt;!-- resize grip &amp; status message --&gt;
&lt;Grid Grid.Row=&quot;4&quot; Background=&quot;{DynamicResource Accent}&quot;&gt;
    &lt;Grid.ColumnDefinitions&gt;
        &lt;ColumnDefinition Width=&quot;*&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;ColumnDefinition Width=&quot;Auto&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/Grid.ColumnDefinitions&gt;
    &lt;TextBlock x:Name=&quot;Status&quot; Text=&quot;{TemplateBinding StatusMessage}&quot; Margin=&quot;3&quot; Foreground=&quot;White&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;Path x:Name=&quot;ResizeGrip&quot; Visibility=&quot;Collapsed&quot; Width=&quot;12&quot; Height=&quot;12&quot; Margin=&quot;1&quot; HorizontalAlignment=&quot;Right&quot; VerticalAlignment=&quot;Bottom&quot;
          Stroke=&quot;{DynamicResource WindowText}&quot;
          StrokeThickness=&quot;1&quot;
          Stretch=&quot;None&quot;
          Grid.Column=&quot;1&quot;
          Data=&quot;F1 M1,10 L3,10 M5,10 L7,10 M9,10 L11,10 M2,9 L2,11 M6,9 L6,11 M10,9 L10,11 M5,6 L7,6 M9,6 L11,6 M6,5 L6,7 M10,5 L10,7 M9,2 L11,2 M10,1 L10,3&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/Grid&gt;
</code></pre>

I plan on making this like the right click panel that slides up in Windows 8 apps. Functionality can be extended in Windows/Controls/ModernWindow.cs. <br />
